&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform API Ownership&lt;/strong&gt; Translate third-party API docs, auth models, webhooks, rate limits, deprecations, permissions, and certification requirements into clear product specs and engineering priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Contracts and Quality&lt;/strong&gt; Define what good integration data looks like: schemas, freshness, completeness, backfills, deduplication, reconciliation, error states, and customer-facing health signals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Setup, Health, and Troubleshooting UX&lt;/strong&gt; Build the setup, consent, status, alerting, and troubleshooting experiences customers and internal teams need to connect accounts quickly and trust the data once it flows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Launch and Operational Readiness&lt;/strong&gt; Own integration launches from discovery through beta, certification, documentation, migration, support enablement, post-launch monitoring, and incident follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Execution&lt;/strong&gt; Partner tightly with engineering, data, CX, sales, legal, privacy/security, and partnerships to unblock complex integrations and make tradeoffs explicit.&lt;/li&gt;
